questions, suggestions or concerns related to our program Support the development and execution of a external stakeholder engagement plan Research and recommend best practices within the area of CSR and benchmark prevailing Desired Skills and ExperienceKEY ATTRIBUTES FOR SUCCESS:   Embodies the highest level of personal and professional integrity and ethics A true passion for Corporate Social Responsibility Maintains a global perspective and is culturally sensitive and aware Influences key members of an organization at all levels Possesses a personally engaging style with excellent written and verbal communication skills Thrives in a collaborative team environment Demonstrates a creative, energetic and motivated spirit Possesses attention to detail while managing simultaneous project in a dynamic environment COMPETENCIES & EXPERIENCE:   Bachelor's degree in Business, Finance or a related field; 3+ years experience in supply chains audits 5+ years' related experience in social responsibility (developing, enforcing, or influencing implementation) Strong communication and presentation skills Ability to clearly articulate goals and objectives Strong information-seeking skills and a drive to make things happen  Ability to understand challenges or underlying concerns, share ideas and develop effective responses or elevate to higher management Ability to work independently and cooperatively in a diverse group  Ability to network, influence, and utilize internal and external resources Ability to exercise a high degree of professionalism  Demonstrated leadership capability, including the ability to motivate and mentor others within work group Ability to lead initiatives and project teams Fluency in English Proficiency in Windows XP, Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel, and AccessAbout this companyCitak - Modern HeadhuntersOur client has helped shape the way people cook and entertain. Our client offers thousands of hand-selected products from around the world including a variet